ed for, the evidence of things not seen.\xe2\x80\x9d</span></span><span class="fn-container">\r\n\t\t<span class="fn-ref">Ibid. November 3, 1898</span><span class="fn-body">\r\n\t\tThe Gospel of Christ was a stumbling-block to the Jews, because they required signs instead of a Saviour; but the Lord would not have His people rest in signs and outward forms. He would not have them wait until every seeming objection is removed before they believe. God will never remove all seeming difficulties from our path. Those who wish to doubt may find opportunity; those who wish to believe will find plenty of evidence on which to base their faith.</span></span><span class="fn-container">\r\n\t\t<span class="fn-ref">The Spirit of Prophecy, Vol. 2, p. 322</span><span class="fn-body">\r\n\t\tHe who waits for entire knowledge before he can exercise faith, will never be blessed of God.</span></span></td></tr><tr><td class="footnote-index"><span id="footnote-reference-ref-17">17.</span></td><td class="footnote-link"><span onclick="footnote_moveToAnchor(\'footnote-tooltip-ref-17\')"> &uarr; </span></td><td class="footnote-text"><span class="fn-container"><span class="fn-ref">Testimonies to Ministers and Gospel Workers, p. 97</span><span class="fn-body">\r\n\t\tGo on a little longer as you have gone, in rejection of the light from heaven, and you are lost.</span></span></td></tr><tr><td class="footnote-index"><span id="footnote-reference-ref-18">18.</span></td><td class="footnote-link"><span onclick="footnote_moveToAnchor(\'footnote-tooltip-ref-18\')"> &uarr; </span></td><td class="footnote-text"><span class="fn-container"><span class="fn-ref">Early Writings, p. 236</span><span class="fn-body">\r\n\t\tThose who had neglected to receive the heavenly message were left in darkness, and God\'s anger was kindled against them, because they would not receive the light which He had sent them from heaven.</span></span></td></tr><tr><td class="footnote-index"><span id="footnote-reference-ref-19">19.</span></td><td class="footnote-link"><span onclick="footnote_moveToAnchor(\'footnote-tooltip-ref-19\')"> &uarr; </span></td><td class="footnote-text"><span class="fn-container"><span class="fn-ref">The Signs of the Times, November 15, 1899</span><span class="fn-body">\r\n\t\t...if men continue to resist light and evidence, they will cut themselves off from God\'s mercy, and then will come the ministry of wrath. ...The love of God is immeasurable to those who repent, but His justice is firm and uncompromising to those who abuse his long-suffering love.</span></span></td></tr><tr><td class="footnote-index"><span id="footnote-reference-ref-20">20.</span></td><td class="footnote-link"><span onclick="footnote_moveToAnchor(\'footnote-tooltip-ref-20\')"> &uarr; </span></td><td class="footnote-text"><span class="fn-container"><span class="fn-ref">The Youth\xe2\x80\x99s Instructor, February 8, 1894</span><span class="fn-body">\r\n\t\tHow terrible were the consequences of this man\'s [Achan\xe2\x80\x99s] sin. How fearful the work wrought upon his family through his example and influence.</span></span></td></tr><tr><td class="footnote-index"><span id="footnote-reference-ref-21">21.</span></td><td class="footnote-link"><span onclick="footnote_moveToAnchor(\'footnote-tooltip-ref-21\')"> &uarr; </span></td><td class="footnote-text"><span class="fn-container"><span class="fn-ref">Christ\xe2\x80\x99s Object Lessons, p. 224</span><span class="fn-body">\r\n\t\tMany there are who allow their wives or their husbands to prevent them from heeding the call of God.</span></span><span class="fn-container">\r\n\t\t<span class="fn-ref">Ibid. p. 225</span><span class="fn-body">\r\n\t\tAll these refuse the Saviour\'s call because they fear division in the family circle. They suppose that in refusing to obey God they are insuring the peace and prosperity of the home; but this is a delusion.</span></span></td></tr><tr><td class="footnote-index"><span id="footnote-reference-ref-22">22.</span></